#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:5
msgid "Samsung Galaxy Book Driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:7
msgid "Joshua Grisham <josh@joshuagrisham.com>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:9
msgid ""
"This is a Linux x86 platform driver for Samsung Galaxy Book series notebook "
"devices which utilizes Samsung's ``SCAI`` ACPI device in order to control "
"extra features and receive various notifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:14
msgid "Supported devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:16
msgid ""
"Any device with one of the supported ACPI device IDs should be supported. "
"This covers most of the \"Samsung Galaxy Book\" series notebooks that are "
"currently available as of this writing, and could include other Samsung "
"notebook devices as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:22
msgid "Status"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:24
msgid "The following features are currently supported:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:26
msgid ":ref:`Keyboard backlight <keyboard-backlight>` control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:27
msgid ""
":ref:`Performance mode <performance-mode>` control implemented using the "
"platform profile interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:29
msgid ""
":ref:`Battery charge control end threshold <battery-charge-control-end-"
"threshold>` (stop charging battery at given percentage value) implemented as "
"a battery hook"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:32
msgid ""
":ref:`Firmware Attributes <firmware-attributes>` to allow control of various "
"device settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:34
msgid ""
":ref:`Handling of Fn hotkeys <keyboard-hotkey-actions>` for various actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:35
msgid ""
":ref:`Handling of ACPI notifications and hotkeys <acpi-notifications-and-"
"hotkey-actions>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:38
msgid ""
"Because different models of these devices can vary in their features, there "
"is logic built within the driver which attempts to test each implemented "
"feature for a valid response before enabling its support (registering "
"additional devices or extensions, adding sysfs attributes, etc). Therefore, "
"it can be important to note that not all features may be supported for your "
"particular device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:44
msgid ""
"The following features might be possible to implement but will require "
"additional investigation and are therefore not supported at this time:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:47
msgid "\"Dolby Atmos\" mode for the speakers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:48
msgid ""
"\"Outdoor Mode\" for increasing screen brightness on models with ``SAM0427``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:49
msgid "\"Silent Mode\" on models with ``SAM0427``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:54
msgid "Keyboard backlight"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:56
msgid ""
"A new LED class named ``samsung-galaxybook::kbd_backlight`` is created which "
"will then expose the device using the standard sysfs-based LED interface at "
"``/sys/class/leds/samsung-galaxybook::kbd_backlight``. Brightness can be "
"controlled by writing the desired value to the ``brightness`` sysfs "
"attribute or with any other desired userspace utility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:63
msgid ""
"Most of these devices have an ambient light sensor which also turns off the "
"keyboard backlight under well-lit conditions. This behavior does not seem "
"possible to control at this time, but can be good to be aware of."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:70
msgid "Performance mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:72
msgid ""
"This driver implements the Documentation/userspace-api/sysfs-"
"platform_profile.rst interface for working with the \"performance mode\" "
"function of the Samsung ACPI device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:76
msgid ""
"Mapping of each Samsung \"performance mode\" to its respective platform "
"profile is performed dynamically by the driver, as not all models support "
"all of the same performance modes. Your device might have one or more of the "
"following mappings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:80
msgid "\"Silent\" maps to ``low-power``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:81
msgid "\"Quiet\" maps to ``quiet``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:82
msgid "\"Optimized\" maps to ``balanced``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:83
msgid "\"High performance\" maps to ``performance``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:85
msgid ""
"The result of the mapping can be printed in the kernel log when the module "
"is loaded. Supported profiles can also be retrieved from ``/sys/firmware/"
"acpi/platform_profile_choices``, while ``/sys/firmware/acpi/"
"platform_profile`` can be used to read or write the currently selected "
"profile."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:91
msgid ""
"The ``balanced`` platform profile will be set during module load if no "
"profile has been previously set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:97
msgid "Battery charge control end threshold"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:99
msgid ""
"This platform driver will add the ability to set the battery's charge "
"control end threshold, but does not have the ability to set a start "
"threshold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:102
msgid ""
"This feature is typically called \"Battery Saver\" by the various Samsung "
"applications in Windows, but in Linux we have implemented the standardized "
"\"charge control threshold\" sysfs interface on the battery device to allow "
"for controlling this functionality from the userspace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:107
msgid ""
"The sysfs attribute ``/sys/class/power_supply/BAT1/"
"charge_control_end_threshold`` can be used to read or set the desired charge "
"end threshold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:111
msgid ""
"If you wish to maintain interoperability with the Samsung Settings "
"application in Windows, then you should set the value to 100 to represent "
"\"off\", or enable the feature using only one of the following values: 50, "
"60, 70, 80, or 90. Otherwise, the driver will accept any value between 1 and "
"100 as the percentage that you wish the battery to stop charging at."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:118
msgid ""
"Some devices have been observed as automatically \"turning off\" the charge "
"control end threshold if an input value of less than 30 is given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:124
msgid "Firmware Attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:126
msgid ""
"The following enumeration-typed firmware attributes are set up by this "
"driver and should be accessible under ``/sys/class/firmware-attributes/"
"samsung-galaxybook/attributes/`` if your device supports them:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:131
msgid "``power_on_lid_open`` (device should power on when the lid is opened)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:132
msgid ""
"``usb_charging``  (USB ports can deliver power to connected devices even "
"when the device is powered off or in a low sleep state)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:134
msgid "``block_recording`` (blocks access to camera and microphone)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:136
msgid ""
"All of these attributes are simple boolean-like enumeration values which use "
"0 to represent \"off\" and 1 to represent \"on\". Use the ``current_value`` "
"attribute to get or change the setting on the device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:140
msgid ""
"Note that when ``block_recording`` is updated, the input device \"Samsung "
"Galaxy Book Lens Cover\" will receive a ``SW_CAMERA_LENS_COVER`` switch "
"event which reflects the current state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:147
msgid "Keyboard hotkey actions (i8042 filter)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:149
msgid ""
"The i8042 filter will swallow the keyboard events for the Fn+F9 hotkey "
"(Multi- level keyboard backlight toggle) and Fn+F10 hotkey (Block recording "
"toggle) and instead execute their actions within the driver itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:153
msgid ""
"Fn+F9 will cycle through the brightness levels of the keyboard backlight. A "
"notification will be sent using "
"``led_classdev_notify_brightness_hw_changed`` so that the userspace can be "
"aware of the change. This mimics the behavior of other existing devices "
"where the brightness level is cycled internally by the embedded controller "
"and then reported via a notification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:159
msgid ""
"Fn+F10 will toggle the value of the \"block recording\" setting, which "
"blocks or allows usage of the built-in camera and microphone (and generates "
"the same Lens Cover switch event mentioned above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:166
msgid "ACPI notifications and hotkey actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:168
msgid ""
"ACPI notifications will generate ACPI netlink events under the device class "
"``samsung-galaxybook`` and bus ID matching the Samsung ACPI device ID found "
"on your device. The events can be received using userspace tools such as "
"``acpi_listen`` and ``acpid``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/samsung-galaxybook.rst:173
msgid ""
"The Fn+F11 Performance mode hotkey will be handled by the driver; each "
"keypress will cycle to the next available platform profile."
msgstr ""
